1
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:13,733
<i>- Mom!
- Mom!</i>

2
00:00:13,867 --> 00:00:17,433
<i>She was exactly like this
the first time Dad left us.</i>

3
00:00:17,567 --> 00:00:19,767
<i>I hurt Andeng's feelings
earlier.</i>

4
00:00:19,900 --> 00:00:23,300
<i>Did you explain to her properly
why I'm here?</i>

5
00:00:23,433 --> 00:00:25,700
<i>I really need to tell the truth.</i>

6
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:26,633
<i> What truth?</i>

7
00:00:26,767 --> 00:00:30,300
<i> Coleen didn't push Jessica.</i>

8
00:00:30,433 --> 00:00:32,167
<i> Atty. Salazar just called.</i>

9
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:33,600
<i> He already spoke with Timo.</i>

10
00:00:33,767 --> 00:00:35,667
<i>Has Timo already withdrawn his
statement?</i>

11
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:38,067
<i> The court dismissed the case.</i>

12
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:39,367
<i> Coleen is a free woman.</i>

13
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:40,867
<i> Does Dad know?</i>

14
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:44,700
<i> I want to go to Dad.</i>

15
00:00:44,833 --> 00:00:46,733
<i>Maybe he's not mad
at me anymore.</i>

16
00:00:46,867 --> 00:00:49,667
<i>Dear, he knows you didn't do
anything wrong.</i>

17
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:52,533
<i>If he knows,
then why did he leave?</i>

18
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:57,267
Coleen, honey...

19
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:02,300
The news just came out that you
won't be going to jail.

20
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:06,033
Why don't we just dwell on
that for today?

21
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:10,800
Uncle, the celebration doesn't
feel complete without Dad here.

22
00:01:10,967 --> 00:01:12,967
I want us to make things right.

23
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:15,433
If there's an issue,
we should talk about it.

24
00:01:15,567 --> 00:01:17,667
I want him to come home.

25
00:01:18,900 --> 00:01:20,400
Dear, you can't.

26
00:01:20,533 --> 00:01:22,267
Why not?

27
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:25,533
I don't understand why Dad left.

28
00:01:25,667 --> 00:01:27,967
Why you didn't fight for him.

29
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:30,067
Coleen, that's enough.

30
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:34,033
Jeff, I want to fight for Dad!

31
00:01:34,167 --> 00:01:36,033
I'm not giving up!

32
00:01:36,167 --> 00:01:39,867
So please, Mom, let's go.
Let's go to Dad, please.

33
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,567
- Mom.
- Coleen, stop!

34
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:45,433
I said you can't!

35
00:01:47,667 --> 00:01:49,167
We are not going to see
your father,

36
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:50,933
and he is not coming back!

37
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,467
Manuel, here.

38
00:02:09,033 --> 00:02:11,000
Sorry about the food.

39
00:02:11,133 --> 00:02:12,767
I just ordered it.

40
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:16,033
I couldn't cook.

41
00:02:17,967 --> 00:02:19,933
I'm not feeling well.

42
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:26,300
Hazel, can you stop
with the drama?

43
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:28,367
I know you were just acting
in front of that Attorney,

44
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,667
so you wouldn't get caught
for paying off Timo.

45
00:02:33,933 --> 00:02:36,400
Is that really what you think
of me?

46
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:37,800
Acting?

47
00:02:42,233 --> 00:02:45,433
I don't know how to explain
this to you but...

48
00:02:45,567 --> 00:02:49,600
ever since our daughter died...

49
00:02:51,367 --> 00:02:57,900
all I ever wanted was justice
for what happened to her.

50
00:02:58,033 --> 00:02:59,733
But in the end,

51
00:03:00,233 --> 00:03:03,300
I'm the one who made a way
to get Timo

52
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:07,700
to withdraw his statement
so Coleen wouldn't go to jail.

53
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,767
And I wonder...

54
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:16,200
did I really give Jessica
justice?

55
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:22,467
I feel guilty that I had
to make that sacrifice.

56
00:03:22,633 --> 00:03:27,500
But knowing how kind
our daughter was...

57
00:03:28,667 --> 00:03:30,433
I know this is what she would
have wanted.

58
00:03:31,467 --> 00:03:35,300
For her sister Coleen
to stay free...

59
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:39,233
to live a good life...

60
00:03:41,933 --> 00:03:45,233
to finally reach her dreams.

61
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:47,500
I thought...

62
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:50,000
if Coleen is free,
then in a way,

63
00:03:50,133 --> 00:03:53,167
I also gave justice to what
happened to Jessica.

64
00:04:06,933 --> 00:04:10,533
Thank you for your sacrifice,
Hazel.

65
00:04:14,167 --> 00:04:16,733
I'll owe you that for the rest
of my life.

66
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,133
I'm sorry.

67
00:04:36,267 --> 00:04:37,367
I'm sorry.

68
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:40,067
I didn't mean to shout.

69
00:04:41,933 --> 00:04:47,300
Coleen, honey, please try
to understand your mom.

70
00:04:47,433 --> 00:04:50,133
Uncle, I don't understand.

71
00:04:51,167 --> 00:04:53,700
I don't understand
why Dad did that.

72
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:56,267
Why he left.
Why he abandoned us!

73
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:59,867
Why Mom didn't even fight
for him!

74
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,900
Dear, didn't we already explain?

75
00:05:03,067 --> 00:05:04,667
Explain what?

76
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:07,000
That Hazel hurts herself,

77
00:05:07,133 --> 00:05:08,800
so she needs someone
to watch her?

78
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:13,867
Hazel is his wife, dear.

79
00:05:15,233 --> 00:05:16,767
They're married.

80
00:05:18,967 --> 00:05:25,567
He has an obligation
to take care of her.

81
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:29,033
Mom, do you hear yourself?

82
00:05:29,167 --> 00:05:32,467
Since when did you start caring
about Hazel?

83
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:36,667
And Mom, didn't you have a plan?

84
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,400
Dad was supposed to get
an annulment,

85
00:05:39,533 --> 00:05:42,433
and then we'd finally
be a real family.

86
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:46,367
What happened to that plan?

87
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,533
It's gone?

88
00:05:48,667 --> 00:05:50,100
Just like that?

89
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:52,300
I'm not stupid!

90
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:55,467
Coleen, instead of fighting Mom,

91
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,733
can you just accept
that Dad is gone?

92
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,933
This is our reality now.

93
00:06:02,067 --> 00:06:03,533
Dad went back to his wife.

94
00:06:03,667 --> 00:06:04,467
Us...

95
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:07,100
all there's left to do
is to move on.

96
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:08,200
How?

97
00:06:09,767 --> 00:06:11,933
Dad left us again.

98
00:06:13,233 --> 00:06:16,233
It was better the first time.
I was a baby.

99
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:18,600
I couldn't feel anything.

100
00:06:18,733 --> 00:06:20,233
But this...

101
00:06:20,367 --> 00:06:22,567
He made me feel like I had
a father,

102
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:24,833
only to leave me again!

103
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,233
Coleen.

104
00:06:28,367 --> 00:06:29,500
Sweetie.

105
00:06:39,533 --> 00:06:41,500
I already did what you told me
to do.

106
00:06:42,767 --> 00:06:44,167
Congratulations.

107
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:46,600
So you can keep your end
of the deal.

108
00:06:47,633 --> 00:06:52,700
I hope you keep yours, too.

109
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:54,933
You promised to support
my family,

110
00:06:55,067 --> 00:06:57,100
that you wouldn't touch them.

111
00:06:57,233 --> 00:06:58,733
On one condition.

112
00:07:00,300 --> 00:07:02,100
What is it this time?

113
00:07:02,233 --> 00:07:03,633
Don't worry.

114
00:07:03,767 --> 00:07:05,833
It's simple.

115
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,767
Just keep your mouth shut.

116
00:07:09,867 --> 00:07:11,100
Stay quiet.

117
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,933
No visitors.

118
00:07:16,167 --> 00:07:18,533
Especially Coleen
and her family.

119
00:07:19,633 --> 00:07:23,733
And don't you dare tell anyone
that I paid you to frame Coleen.

120
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:24,967
And most of all.

121
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:27,167
Why did you have to threaten me?

122
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:30,467
You threatened me just to make
me retract my statement?

123
00:07:31,533 --> 00:07:32,867
Threatened?

124
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,800
Strong word.

125
00:07:36,867 --> 00:07:38,200
Fine.

126
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:39,967
I'll own it.

127
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:44,267
Never ever talk
to Coleen's camp.

128
00:07:45,767 --> 00:07:48,467
Don't even try.

129
00:07:48,633 --> 00:07:53,067
You know I have eyes inside
this place.

130
00:08:00,067 --> 00:08:01,600
Or else,

131
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:03,500
it won't just be you who gets
hurt.

132
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,433
Your whole family will be
affected.

133
00:08:06,567 --> 00:08:10,200
So if I were you,
I'd stay quiet.

134
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:11,867
Don't try anything.

135
00:08:13,267 --> 00:08:14,567
Do you understand?

136
00:08:32,133 --> 00:08:33,033
Coleen.

137
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:42,267
Coleen, I didn't mean to argue
earlier.

138
00:08:43,967 --> 00:08:45,200
I'm sorry, okay?

139
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:48,000
Sweetie...

140
00:08:51,967 --> 00:08:54,067
Please don't be mad at us.

141
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:58,267
I'm not mad at you, sis.
Or at you, bro.

142
00:08:59,267 --> 00:09:01,500
I'm not mad at Mom either.

143
00:09:02,567 --> 00:09:04,300
I'm just frustrated because
until now,

144
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:05,900
I still don't get it.

145
00:09:06,967 --> 00:09:08,267
Why?

146
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:12,600
Why did you accept so quickly
that Dad left us again?

147
00:09:12,733 --> 00:09:15,567
Why does it feel like you
and Mom understand each other?

148
00:09:15,700 --> 00:09:18,400
Is it just me, or do you know
something I don't?

149
00:09:20,567 --> 00:09:21,767
Dear, nothing.

150
00:09:23,067 --> 00:09:25,067
What are you saying? Nothing.

151
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:30,233
Maybe Jeff and I are just older.
More experienced.

152
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,867
So for us,

153
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:38,667
it's easier to accept and
understand our situation now.

154
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,800
I don't know, sis.

155
00:09:43,967 --> 00:09:47,833
I just want to be sure
that Dad isn't mad at me.

156
00:09:47,967 --> 00:09:52,200
And I just want to know if he's
happy that I'm not in jail.

157
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:53,433
He is happy.

158
00:09:57,133 --> 00:09:58,767
How do you know?

159
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:05,000
Because that's how Dad is,
right?

160
00:10:05,133 --> 00:10:08,267
Whenever we're happy,
he's happy too.

161
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:13,600
So now that we're happy because
your case was dismissed,

162
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:16,833
he feels the same for sure.

163
00:10:16,967 --> 00:10:18,433
He's happy, too.

164
00:10:22,033 --> 00:10:24,533
I hope I get to hear him say
that.

165
00:10:35,967 --> 00:10:36,867
Mom,

166
00:10:37,667 --> 00:10:40,533
thanks for coming here with me.

167
00:10:40,667 --> 00:10:43,233
Even though I fought
with you the other day.

168
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:45,633
It's nothing, sweetheart.

169
00:10:47,667 --> 00:10:49,933
I also wanted to talk to Timo.

170
00:10:52,767 --> 00:10:54,633
Who's my visitor again, boss?

171
00:11:05,567 --> 00:11:06,533
Timo?

172
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:19,433
Sir, take me back inside.
I don't want to talk to them.

173
00:11:19,567 --> 00:11:21,100
Timo, wait.

174
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:23,900
We didn't come here to fight.

175
00:11:24,567 --> 00:11:27,200
We came to thank you
for what you did.

176
00:11:28,367 --> 00:11:29,533
Timo.

177
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:33,767
Thank you so much for your help.

178
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:36,367
Sorry.

179
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:42,267
<i>Don't you dare try anything.
I have eyes inside this place.</i>

180
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,200
Timo, wait.

181
00:11:50,633 --> 00:11:52,267
Don't come back here again,
okay?

182
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:07,333
Mom, why didn't Timo talk to us?

183
00:12:08,467 --> 00:12:09,500
I wonder, too.

184
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:12,167
He looked angry.

185
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:14,867
But at least, he apologized.

186
00:12:16,733 --> 00:12:19,300
At least he admitted
what he did.

187
00:12:20,433 --> 00:12:22,967
Maybe that's enough for closure.

188
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:24,767
Right, Mom?

189
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:27,300
You can start again, dear.

190
00:12:27,433 --> 00:12:30,400
It's just Dad that I don't have
closure with.

191
00:12:30,533 --> 00:12:33,133
But of course,
I don't want closure with him.

192
00:12:33,267 --> 00:12:34,733
He's still my dad.

193
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,600
Are we going to argue about this
again?

194
00:12:38,733 --> 00:12:43,933
Mom, all I want is to talk
to him.

195
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,600
Coleen, let's not force it.

196
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:49,900
It's not the right time.

197
00:12:52,067 --> 00:12:53,033
Let's go.

198
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,700
<i>Felma, call me stupid if you
want.</i>

199
00:13:09,833 --> 00:13:13,100
<i>But if this means Coleen's
freedom, fine.</i>

200
00:13:13,233 --> 00:13:14,933
<i> I'll go back to Hazel.</i>

201
00:13:15,067 --> 00:13:16,467
<i> There's another way.</i>

202
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:20,200
<i> All of this is for you.</i>

203
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:23,833
<i>For your life and your
children's future.</i>

204
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,433
<i> Just help us.</i>

205
00:13:25,567 --> 00:13:28,233
<i> Maybe you could talk to Timo?</i>

206
00:13:28,367 --> 00:13:31,467
<i>Ask him to withdraw his
statement against Coleen.</i>

207
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:37,333
<i>I'm sorry, but I can't accept
this.</i>

208
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:57,633
<i>Manuel, I don't want you going
back to Hazel.</i>

209
00:13:57,800 --> 00:13:59,000
<i>Felma, I don't want that either.</i>

210
00:13:59,133 --> 00:14:02,167
<i>But this is the only way
for Coleen to be free.</i>

211
00:14:04,567 --> 00:14:06,300
<i> This is from the court.</i>

212
00:14:06,433 --> 00:14:10,567
<i>A copy of Timo Malabanan's
Affidavit of Recantation.</i>

213
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:16,933
<i> The case has been dismissed.</i>

214
00:14:17,067 --> 00:14:18,700
<i> Coleen is a free woman.</i>

215
00:14:21,367 --> 00:14:24,233
<i>I just don't understand
why Dad left...</i>

216
00:14:24,367 --> 00:14:26,533
<i> why you didn't fight for him.</i>

217
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:35,400
Coleen is free now, Manuel.

218
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,933
But you're the one trapped
with Hazel.

219
00:14:48,533 --> 00:14:51,500
How are we supposed
to face this again?

220
00:15:06,233 --> 00:15:07,167
Jessica...

221
00:15:09,967 --> 00:15:14,067
Was it right for me and
your Aunt Felma...

222
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:16,033
to follow what your mom wanted?

223
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,633
Just so your sister Coleen
wouldn't go to jail?

224
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:27,667
Because I know you wanted
her to be free, right?

225
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:33,400
Dear, you'll still get justice
for what happened to you.

226
00:15:35,833 --> 00:15:38,067
As long as that driver
ends up in jail.

227
00:15:39,700 --> 00:15:40,400
Dear...

228
00:15:41,567 --> 00:15:47,367
I hope that after everything,
you can finally be at peace.

229
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,800
I miss you so much.

230
00:15:56,867 --> 00:16:00,333
You know, until now, I still
can't accept that you're gone.

231
00:16:05,267 --> 00:16:07,000
I love you so, so much.

232
00:16:10,167 --> 00:16:11,967
I love you.

233
00:16:41,700 --> 00:16:45,067
Danio, the bathroom's filthy.

234
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,233
Assign someone to clean it.

235
00:16:46,367 --> 00:16:46,867
Hurry.

236
00:17:09,233 --> 00:17:09,800
Bro!

237
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:11,300
Bro.

238
00:17:12,733 --> 00:17:13,667
The thing we talked about.

239
00:17:16,533 --> 00:17:17,367
Come on.

240
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,000
Thank you. Thank you.

241
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:33,300
What's that for?

242
00:17:33,433 --> 00:17:36,000
I need to write something.

243
00:17:36,133 --> 00:17:38,067
So if anything happens to me,

244
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:43,767
it'll reach the person who needs
to know the information.

245
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:04,900
You've been drinking more often.

246
00:18:05,033 --> 00:18:09,800
Well, coffee's really good
for sobering up, right, Ma'am?

247
00:18:09,933 --> 00:18:11,967
Didang, stop that.

248
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:15,233
I'm only drinking because
we're celebrating.

249
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:20,667
Finally, we can breathe again.

250
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:23,200
Coleen is totally free.

251
00:18:23,367 --> 00:18:27,367
Thank God we got
through that trial.

252
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:28,533
Of course, Ma'am.

253
00:18:28,667 --> 00:18:30,333
And from the start,

254
00:18:30,467 --> 00:18:35,600
we were confident my girl
would be cleared.

255
00:18:35,733 --> 00:18:37,967
She could never do what
they accused her of.

256
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:42,267
I don't know why Timo
dragged Coleen into it.

257
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:44,267
Stop being so negative.

258
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:49,200
Let's just think about
the next chapter.

259
00:18:49,333 --> 00:18:51,400
Oh, yes, the next chapter,

260
00:18:51,533 --> 00:18:55,300
where Sir Manuel is no longer
part of it.

261
00:18:55,467 --> 00:18:56,733
Didang, seriously?

262
00:18:56,867 --> 00:18:59,100
You really had to bring that up?

263
00:18:59,233 --> 00:19:01,533
Can we just move on, please?

264
00:19:01,667 --> 00:19:03,333
Move on right away, Ma'am?

265
00:19:03,467 --> 00:19:05,100
No, cannot be.

266
00:19:05,233 --> 00:19:06,667
Borrow one from two.

267
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:09,800
If I get separation anxiety,
how much more you?

268
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,600
Tell me the truth.

269
00:19:13,733 --> 00:19:15,433
Didang, I told you.

270
00:19:15,567 --> 00:19:16,667
Stop it already.

271
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:18,067
You're repeating it again!

272
00:19:20,633 --> 00:19:21,700
Stop being so nosy!

273
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:26,067
Why don't we talk about
Sir Noah instead?

274
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:27,400
There.

275
00:19:27,533 --> 00:19:28,967
There!

276
00:19:29,133 --> 00:19:30,600
That's better.

277
00:19:30,867 --> 00:19:32,100
Let's keep the good vibes.

278
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:35,700
We're actually meeting later.

279
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:38,533
Eat breakfast first, Ma'am.

280
00:19:38,667 --> 00:19:40,133
Wait, there's more here.

281
00:19:40,267 --> 00:19:41,367
Thank you.

282
00:19:41,633 --> 00:19:43,167
I'm fine with just coffee.

283
00:19:45,633 --> 00:19:49,167
Ma'am, anyone would
be happy with coffee,

284
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:51,367
especially if they have
a boyfriend, right?

285
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:55,933
Because you have someone
to squeeze or touch.

286
00:19:56,067 --> 00:19:57,767
Right, Ma'am?

287
00:19:57,900 --> 00:19:59,433
What are you saying? Stop it.

288
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:05,267
Oh, can you get my medicine?

289
00:20:05,433 --> 00:20:07,167
For my headache.

290
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:10,233
Oh, okay.

291
00:20:10,367 --> 00:20:11,767
Drink more, Ma'am.

292
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:13,067
I'll get it now.

293
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:24,233
Manuel, your...

294
00:20:25,633 --> 00:20:27,867
Here's your towel.

295
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:31,933
Do you want me to help you
shower?

296
00:20:32,233 --> 00:20:32,933
No, it's fine.

297
00:20:33,067 --> 00:20:34,233
Thank you. I can manage.

298
00:20:36,067 --> 00:20:38,033
Are you still shy around me?

299
00:20:38,267 --> 00:20:41,500
I'm a nurse, and we're married.

300
00:20:42,233 --> 00:20:44,533
It's okay if I bathe you.

301
00:20:44,667 --> 00:20:45,467
No, really.

302
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:46,967
I can do it.

303
00:20:47,100 --> 00:20:48,967
Just leave the towel.

304
00:20:49,100 --> 00:20:50,467
You sure?

305
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:51,800
Yes, I can manage.

306
00:20:54,533 --> 00:20:58,567
All right. Just call me
if you need anything.

307
00:20:58,700 --> 00:20:59,267
Here.

308
00:21:02,333 --> 00:21:05,233
Be careful moving around, okay?

309
00:21:05,367 --> 00:21:06,033
Okay.

310
00:21:06,167 --> 00:21:07,967
Please close the door.

311
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:08,933
Sure.

312
00:21:38,133 --> 00:21:39,633
Dad.

313
00:21:39,767 --> 00:21:41,733
Hello, Jeffrey.

314
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:43,133
<i> Son, how are you?</i>

315
00:21:43,267 --> 00:21:45,333
Of course, Dad,
I'm happy for Coleen.

316
00:21:45,467 --> 00:21:47,067
I'm sure you are, too.

317
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,300
Of course, I am.

318
00:21:48,433 --> 00:21:52,100
It's just that Coleen keeps
asking a lot about you.

319
00:21:52,233 --> 00:21:54,233
And, of course, I can't
tell her the truth.

320
00:21:54,367 --> 00:21:55,800
<i> Let it be.</i>

321
00:21:55,933 --> 00:21:58,867
What matters is that
Coleen is free

322
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,400
and can start a new life.

323
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:03,767
<i> You take care of her, okay?</i>

324
00:22:03,900 --> 00:22:05,167
Always, Dad. Don't worry.

325
00:22:05,300 --> 00:22:08,133
<i> Son, is your Mom there?</i>

326
00:22:08,267 --> 00:22:10,033
Can I talk to her?

327
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:19,667
Coleen, where do you
want to go today?

328
00:22:21,900 --> 00:22:25,033
You want to go to the mall
with Jeff and me?

329
00:22:25,267 --> 00:22:26,767
I'd like that.

330
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:29,933
But can we stop by
Jessica's grave first?

331
00:22:30,067 --> 00:22:32,133
Of course.

332
00:22:32,267 --> 00:22:35,400
Mom, want to come with us?

333
00:22:35,533 --> 00:22:36,600
Yes, Mom.

334
00:22:36,733 --> 00:22:38,867
The more the merrier.

335
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:40,233
No.

336
00:22:40,367 --> 00:22:42,133
Kids, you go ahead.

337
00:22:42,267 --> 00:22:44,200
I'm going out with
your Uncle Noah.

338
00:22:47,167 --> 00:22:50,000
What if we just go with you?

339
00:22:50,167 --> 00:22:53,867
I'm sure Uncle Noah
will treat us.

340
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,867
Mom, look at Andrea
freeloading again.

341
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:58,867
But maybe we can do that?

342
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:01,133
Isn't Uncle Noah generous?

343
00:23:01,267 --> 00:23:02,567
See?

344
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:06,433
Saying those things,
but wanting a free meal, too.

345
00:23:06,567 --> 00:23:09,100
And you've been
eating a lot lately.

346
00:23:09,233 --> 00:23:11,600
Noah and I have other plans.

347
00:23:11,733 --> 00:23:13,967
Next time we'll go
out together, okay?

348
00:23:17,267 --> 00:23:19,200
- You two, stop...
- Mom.

349
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:20,200
Eat your breakfast, son.

350
00:23:20,333 --> 00:23:22,200
No, I'll finish
my workout first.

351
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:23,433
You're working out?

352
00:23:23,567 --> 00:23:24,367
Yes.

353
00:23:24,500 --> 00:23:25,167
Go eat already.

354
00:23:25,300 --> 00:23:27,067
Stop it, both of you. Eat.

355
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:29,700
- It doesn't show, right?
- No, it doesn't.

356
00:23:29,833 --> 00:23:32,000
Oh, wait.

357
00:23:32,133 --> 00:23:33,100
I need to check something.

358
00:23:33,233 --> 00:23:37,567
The plants in the garden.

359
00:23:39,233 --> 00:23:41,800
Mom gardens now?

360
00:23:41,933 --> 00:23:43,633
Dad got the chance
to call you, Mom.

361
00:23:46,233 --> 00:23:47,167
Hello, love.

362
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:53,500
You have some nerve!

363
00:23:53,633 --> 00:23:56,600
Who told you you could
visit my daughter's grave?

364
00:23:56,767 --> 00:23:57,733
Hazel, stop!

365
00:23:57,867 --> 00:23:58,733
Dad!

366
00:24:00,933 --> 00:24:01,533
Andeng.

367
00:24:02,967 --> 00:24:05,300
I left without saying goodbye.

368
00:24:05,433 --> 00:24:08,433
Dad, you didn't
need to say goodbye.

369
00:24:08,567 --> 00:24:11,967
Dad, please come home.
